636
00:45:36,736 --> 00:45:38,938
That's enough for me.

637
00:46:03,763 --> 00:46:06,165
Doctor Woo, you need to come quickly.

638
00:46:08,434 --> 00:46:09,902
Was there a problem during treatment?

639
00:46:09,902 --> 00:46:11,304
No, he's been fine lately.

640
00:46:11,304 --> 00:46:13,773
I thought he was receiving treatment well.

641
00:46:13,773 --> 00:46:14,607
Come quickly.

642
00:46:15,074 --> 00:46:17,210
Excuse me, please, excuse me.

643
00:46:31,457 --> 00:46:32,625
Sir, what are you doing?

644
00:46:33,392 --> 00:46:34,927
Doctor.

645
00:46:35,995 --> 00:46:37,897
Please let me out.

646
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:41,534
Sir.

647
00:46:46,272 --> 00:46:47,740
Let her go,

648
00:46:49,075 --> 00:46:50,109
and talk to me. Talk to me.

649
00:46:52,311 --> 00:46:53,679
I'll listen to everything
you have to say.

650
00:46:56,449 --> 00:46:58,518
You don't want anyone
to get hurt either, do you?

651
00:47:15,568 --> 00:47:16,669
Doctor.

652
00:47:19,238 --> 00:47:23,242
I don't care if I die like this,
so just let me out of here.

653
00:47:27,880 --> 00:47:29,382
I know it's hard for you,

654
00:47:31,317 --> 00:47:33,352
but if you leave now, the risk
of infection is high, so you can't.

655
00:47:34,921 --> 00:47:38,424
I don't care about any of that.

656
00:47:41,527 --> 00:47:43,262
If you just endure it a little longer,

657
00:47:45,932 --> 00:47:47,433
I'll discharge you after
your treatment is over.

658
00:47:47,433 --> 00:47:48,801
Treatment?

659
00:47:50,236 --> 00:47:52,438
When does it end?

660
00:47:54,474 --> 00:47:56,275
After I'm dead?

661
00:47:57,376 --> 00:48:00,213
I told you to kill me!

662
00:48:00,213 --> 00:48:01,047
Sir.

663
00:48:01,047 --> 00:48:05,218
I kept begging you to kill me!

664
00:48:05,218 --> 00:48:07,887
I... I...

665
00:48:07,887 --> 00:48:11,057
I can't leave here until I die, right?

666
00:48:17,263 --> 00:48:18,931
I know it's hard to get treatment.

667
00:48:19,866 --> 00:48:23,035
But I genuinely want you to live.

668
00:48:24,270 --> 00:48:26,639
Jae-yoon also prays for you every night.

669
00:48:29,242 --> 00:48:31,677
And many of the neighbors
are probably doing the same.

670
00:48:33,579 --> 00:48:34,747
I'll do my best.

671
00:48:35,515 --> 00:48:36,916
So just get a little more treatment and...

672
00:48:36,916 --> 00:48:39,886
Just being kept alive,
is that really living?

673
00:48:40,353 --> 00:48:45,124
In this state, just breathing,
is that what you call living?

674
00:48:45,791 --> 00:48:47,393
I...

675
00:48:47,860 --> 00:48:50,129
I can't even cry anymore.

676
00:48:51,998 --> 00:48:53,933
It's all burned away.

677
00:49:03,609 --> 00:49:04,710
Doctor.

678
00:49:14,020 --> 00:49:15,922
Thank you for everything!

679
00:49:18,624 --> 00:49:19,926
But...

680
00:49:21,160 --> 00:49:25,398
this place is too much of a hell.

681
00:49:42,815 --> 00:49:45,084
After that patient passed away,

682
00:49:45,084 --> 00:49:47,787
Dr. Woo was going through a lot emotionally.

683
00:49:48,221 --> 00:49:51,924
How could someone like that be involved
in the murder of Ms. Kwon Gyeong-mi?

684
00:49:52,825 --> 00:49:57,330
Dr. Woo is a person who does her
best to save patients, more than anyone.

685
00:49:57,330 --> 00:49:59,966
How heartbroken she was
when she lost that patient.

686
00:49:59,966 --> 00:50:01,567
To help my daughter,

687
00:50:02,335 --> 00:50:04,103
she tried very hard.

688
00:50:04,871 --> 00:50:06,205
Although it was in vain.

689
00:50:07,440 --> 00:50:12,411
But what is Dr. Woo being accused of?

690
00:50:13,846 --> 00:50:17,016
She is accused of assisting
in the suicide of patients.

691
00:50:18,651 --> 00:50:19,785
Is there any evidence?

692
00:50:25,992 --> 00:50:27,560
It seems there's no evidence.

693
00:50:32,398 --> 00:50:33,733
The interview is over.

694
00:50:38,704 --> 00:50:39,739
Isn't that a relief?

695
00:50:41,174 --> 00:50:45,278
When you heard it wasn't
Dr. Woo who killed my daughter,

696
00:50:45,611 --> 00:50:47,914
you looked relieved, Detective.

697
00:51:07,519 --> 00:51:11,090
In the past, there was no evidence,
shielding her might have helped,

698
00:51:11,457 --> 00:51:12,291
but it's different now.

699
00:51:12,758 --> 00:51:14,994
An autopsy of Ms. Lee Eun-hee is underway.

700
00:51:16,629 --> 00:51:18,642
When these results come
out, we can prove

701
00:51:18,666 --> 00:51:20,933
Ms. Woo So-jeong's crime even
without your testimony, Father yang.

702
00:51:22,635 --> 00:51:24,637
Well, I don't know
what you're looking for,

703
00:51:25,804 --> 00:51:27,740
but whatever the
autopsy results may be,

704
00:51:27,740 --> 00:51:31,977
will that be direct evidence proving
Ms. Woo So-jeong's guilt?

705
00:51:34,413 --> 00:51:35,748
'Direct evidence.'

706
00:51:38,250 --> 00:51:40,686
You said that when
Ms. Lee Eun-hee passed away,

707
00:51:42,321 --> 00:51:44,823
